OL,3,CNHS chair reflects on six years in the
OL,4,Cjob ahead of retirement
OL,6,F"I joined in 2019, just beginning to
OL,7,Fget my feet under the table. And of
OL,8,Fcourse the pandemic hit in March 2020,
OL,9,Fwhich really just put everything that
OL,10,FI thought was going to be in plan on
OL,11,Fhold.
OL,13,F"I don't want to dwell on it too much,
OL,14,Fbut looking back I think here at NHS
OL,15,Fborders we coped remarkably well - the
OL,16,Fway the staff stepped up to the plate."
