OL,3,CNHS chair reflects on six years in the
OL,4,Cjob ahead of retirement
OL,6,F"I think it's just a feature of where
OL,7,Fwe're at in terms of health needs.
OL,8,FWe're also much better at fixing
OL,9,Fthings, and fixing things costs money.
OL,10,FSo we have to find a balance of how
OL,11,Fwe're going to achieve both those
OL,12,Fthings."
OL,14,FMs Hamilton gave this advice to her
OL,15,Fsuccessor: "Take a step back in the
OL,16,Fearly days. I think that's probably
OL,17,Fthe best thing to do.
