OL,3,CNHS chair reflects on six years in the
OL,4,Cjob ahead of retirement
OL,6,F"When the chair changes there's a
OL,7,Fchange of leadership, obviously, but
OL,8,Fthere's sometimes a change of flavour
OL,9,Fof how the chair might run an
OL,10,Forganisation.
OL,12,F"If I reflect on when I first was
OL,13,Fappointed as chair... I was interim
OL,14,Fchair in the first instance. I looked
OL,15,Facross at other boards, and I thought:
OL,16,F'I couldn't do that and I couldn't do
OL,17,Fthat.'
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/6
